// the setup function runs once when you press reset or power the board
void setup() {
Serial.begin(9600);
}
// the loop function runs over and over again forever
void loop() {
int i = analogRead(A0);
float A;
static int num=0; //
static int curr=0; //
static float max_time[2]={0,0};
static float pi=3.14159265;
num = num + 1;
curr = curr + 1;
static float max_v[2]={0,0};
static int max_num[2];
float w0_hope=1000;
float w0_experimental=w0_hope;
float v = 5.0 * i / 1023.0 ;// i
// Serial.print(v); //
// Serial.println(".\n"); //
// Serial.print(num); //
// Serial.println(" - number \n");
int max=1000;
if (v>max_v[0]) // 2 max
{
max_v[0]=max_v[1];
max_num[0]=max_num[1];
max_time[0]=max_time[1];
max_time[1]=millis();
max_v[1]=v;
max_num[1]=curr;
}
if (num==max) // ,
{
// Serial.print(max_v[0]);
// Serial.println(" ");
// Serial.print(max_v[1]); //
// Serial.println(" Max V, \n");
float dt=max_time[1]-max_time[0];
dt=round(dt);
if (max_v[0]>=max_v[1])
A=max_v[0];
else
A=max_v[1];
Serial.print(A);
Serial.println(" - \n");
int periods=round((dt)*w0_hope/(2*pi));
float w0_experimental = periods*(2*pi)/dt;
Serial.print(w0_experimental);
Serial.println(" - \n");
float tick=dt/periods; //
Serial.print(tick);
Serial.println(" - \n");
max_time[1]=max_time[1]-tick*floor(max_time[1]/tick);
float phi=2*pi-w0_experimental*max_time[1];
Serial.print(phi);
Serial.println(" - \n");
Serial.println(" ---------------------\n");
num=0;
max_v[0]=0;
max_v[1]=0;
max_time[0]=0;
max_time[1]=0;
}
delay(1);
//delay(10); // wait for a second
// Serial.print(millis());
// Serial.println(" - Time\n");
}
